n, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Berwickshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Cameron","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish:","in the Highlands, it is usually a nickname from Gaelic <i>cam</i> ‘crooked, bent’ + <i>sròn</i> ‘nose’.","in the Lowlands it is also a habitational name from any of various places called Cameron, especially in Fife."],"variants":[{"name":"Camren","meanings":["Altered form of Scottish   Cameron  ."]},{"name":"Cambron","meanings":["Spanish (<b>Cambrón</b>): habitational name from any of several places in the provinces of Cáceres and Murcia called Cambrón.","Scottish: altered form of   Cameron  .","French: habitational name from any of the places in Somme and Aisne called Cambron. Alternatively, from a diminutive of <i>c(h)ambre</i> ‘room’ (see   Cambre  )."]},{"name":"Camron","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Cameron  ."]}]},{"name":"Margarete","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from Greek.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margaret","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretha","meanings":["from Greek.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margarethe","meanings":["from Greek.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margarete Cameron was born in 1130, in Scotland as the daughter of John Cameron 3rd Chief of Clan Cameron and Mrs. John Cameron. She married David Haliburton about 1159, in Berwickshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons."},"et":{"1130–":"1130–Surnud","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","1136–1214":"1136–1214","1126–1207":"1126–1207","1152–Male":"1152–Surnud","1160–1207":"1160–1207","–Male":"Surnud","1080–1160":"1080–1160","–Female":"Surnud","1080":"1080","Abt 1152":"umbes 1152","1126":"1126","1214":"1214","1136":"1136","before 1130":"enne 1130","about 1159":"umbes 1159","1130":"1130","1152":"1152","1160":"1160","1207":"1207","Haliburton, Berwickshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Berwickshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","Haliburton, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Berwickshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1130–":"1130–Kuollut","1130–Female":"1130–Kuollut","1136–1214":"1136–1214","1126–1207":"1126–1207","1152–Male":"1152–Kuollut","1160–1207":"1160–1207","–Male":"Kuollut","1080–1160":"1080–1160","–Female":"Kuollut","1080":"1080","Abt 1152":"noin 1152","1126":"1126","1214":"1214","1136":"1136","before 1130":"ennen vuotta 1130","about 1159":"noin 1159","1130":"1130","1152":"1152","1160":"1160","1207":"1207","Haliburton, Berwickshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Berwickshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scotland":"Scotland","Haliburton, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Berwickshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1130–":"1130–Décédée","1130–Female":"1130–